310":"1310","1308":"1308","England":"England, United Kingdom","Hellens, Hertfordshire, England":"Hellens, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Walsh","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Aileen, Dermot, John Patrick, Kieran, Declan, Eamonn, Colm, Donal, Seamus, Siobhan, Brennan.","English and Irish: ethnic name from Middle English <i>walshe</i> (Old English <i>wælisc</i>) ‘foreign, Welsh’. This form of the name was generally more common than   Welsh  , especially in Ireland, where it originally denoted a Welsh-speaking immigrant, in particular any of the Welshmen who arrived in the wake of Strongbow's Anglo-Norman invasion of 1170. In Ireland it is sometimes also a translation of <b>Breathnach</b> ‘Briton’.","English: in Yorkshire and Lancashire the name is sometimes a shortened form of   Walshaw  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Walshe","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Eoin, Murph.","English and Irish: variant of   Walsh  ."]},{"name":"McBratney","meanings":["Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Breatnaigh</b> ‘son of the Briton’ (referring to the Welsh of Strathclyde). Compare   Walsh   and   Galbraith  ."]},{"name":"Welsh","meanings":["Scottish, English, and Irish: ethnic name from Middle English <i>welshe</i> (Old English <i>wēalisc</i>, <i>wēlisc</i>) ‘foreign, Welsh’, for someone from Wales or a speaker of the Welsh language. Compare   Walsh   and   Wallace  .","Americanized form of German   Welsch  .","Americanized form of Ukrainian and Jewish (from Ukraine)   Voloshin   or its Polish variant <b>Wołoszyn</b> (see   Woloszyn  )."]}]},{"name":"Walter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, superseding the native Old English form, <i>Wealdhere</i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Walter Walsh was born in 1308, in England, United Kingdom. He married Mrs Walter Walsh in 1324, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1308–":"1308–Surnud","1310–Female":"1310–Surnud","1322–1357":"1322–1357","1308–Male":"1308–Surnud","1324":"1324","1357":"1357","1322":"1322","1310":"1310","1308":"1308","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hellens, Hertfordshire, England":"Hellens, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1308–":"1308–Kuollut","1310–Female":"1310–Kuollut","1322–1357":"1322–1357","1308–Male":"1308–Kuollut","1324":"1324","1357":"1357","1322":"1322","1310":"1310","1308":"1308","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Hellens, Hertfordshire, England":"Hellens, Herefordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1308–":"1308–Décédé","1310–Female":"1310–Décédée","1322–1357":"1322–1357","1308–Male":"1308–Décédé","1324":"1324","1357":"1357","1322":"1322","1310":"1310","1308":"1308","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Hellens, Hertfordshire, England":"Hellens, Herefordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Walter Walsh est né en 1308, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a épousé Mrs Walter Walsh en 1324, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"1308–":"1308–Verstorben","1310–Female":"1310–Verstorben","1322–1357":"1322–1357","1308–Male":"1308–Verstorben","1324":"1324","1357":"1357","1322":"1322","1310":"1310","1308":"1308","England":"England, United Kingdom","Hellens, Hertfordshire, England":"Hellens, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSum